==Jamaica==
Jamaica's three counties were established in 1758 to facilitate the holding of courts along the lines of the British [[county court]] system, with each county having a county town.<ref name="JPN">{{cite book |last1= Higman |first1= B. W. |last2= Hudson |first2= B. J. |title= Jamaican Place Names |url= http://www.uwipress.com/reviews/jamaican-place-names |location= Mona, Jamaica |year= 2009 |publisher= University of the West Indies Press |page= 31 |isbn= 978-976-640-306-5 }}</ref> The counties have no current administrative relevance.
